# YAML spec

Draw payloads are defined by two related specifications. Use **both** when adding fields, fixtures, or export behavior; reconcile differences via `docs/spec/odl-gap-report.md` (ADR-012).

## Specifications

| Spec | Role | Local copy | Upstream |
|------|------|------------|----------|
| **HA drawcustom** | What Home Assistant’s `drawcustom` service accepts today | `docs/spec/supported_types.md` | [OpenEPaperLink HA integration — supported_types.md](https://github.com/OpenEPaperLink/Home_Assistant_Integration/blob/main/docs/drawcustom/supported_types.md) |
| **OpenDisplay Language (ODL)** | Canonical forward name for the same YAML element list (WIP) | — (diff only) | [opendisplay.org — Open Display Language](https://opendisplay.org/protocol/open-display-language.html) |

**Wire protocol (not YAML):** [OpenDisplay Basic Standard](https://opendisplay.org/protocol/basic-standard.html) — display announcement, `colour_scheme`, packet encoding; maps to editor display config (ADR-012).

**Home Assistant `drawcustom` integrations** (custom components — payload shape matches this editor):

| Integration | Service |
|-------------|---------|
| [OpenEPaperLink HA](https://github.com/OpenEPaperLink/Home_Assistant_Integration) | `open_epaper_link.drawcustom` |
| [OpenDisplay HA](https://github.com/OpenDisplay/Home_Assistant_Integration) | `opendisplay.drawcustom` |

The built-in [core OpenDisplay integration](https://www.home-assistant.io/integrations/opendisplay/) uses `upload_image` only — not `drawcustom`.

When ODL and the vendored HA spec disagree, follow ADR-012 extension rules and update the gap report. Do not bulk-replace `supported_types.md` from ODL until upstream stabilizes.

## HA-clean export rules

YAML copied for Home Assistant must contain **only** valid drawcustom / ODL fields:

- No designer metadata fields
- No `preview_data_url` or similar preview hacks
- No YAML comments added by the designer for asset substitution
- Template strings preserved verbatim (`{{ ... }}`, `{% ... %}`)
- YamlEditor autocomplete must scaffold `{{ }}` / `{% %}` closers; inner completions must not add closing delimiters (ADR-009)

## Service options (top-level, not per-element)

`background`, `rotate`, `dither`, `ttl`, `dry-run` — modeled separately from element payload (HA + ODL service tables).

## Designer templates vs minimal HA YAML

HA allows **optional** position fields (e.g. `text.y` defaults to auto-placement per `supported_types.md` / ODL). **Minimal** golden fixtures in `tests/fixtures/spec/*-minimal.yaml` must stay valid for the schema and stay in sync with `src/core/schema/elementTemplates.ts` (see `tests/core/schema/elementTemplates.test.ts`).

**Add Element** templates are **not** minimal exports — they must include designer-friendly defaults so new elements are immediately editable on canvas:

- Include explicit coordinates where drag/nudge depends on them (`text`: `x` + `y`; `line`: `y_start` / `y_end`; etc.).
- When extending a type, update **both** `ELEMENT_TYPE_INSERTIONS` and the matching `*-minimal.yaml` fixture if the minimal contract changes.

**Imported or hand-edited YAML** may still omit optional coords. Canvas interaction must not silently ignore vertical moves:

- `translateElement` in `src/ui/lib/element-geometry.ts` uses `applyAxisDelta` to **materialize** omitted numeric coordinates on drag/nudge using the same defaults as the renderer (e.g. missing `text.y` → `0` before applying `dy`).
- Pass canvas `{ width, height }` into `translateElement` for `plot` bounds whose omitted `x_end` / `y_end` default to canvas size.

Do not strip optional fields from HA export solely to add designer defaults — export remains HA-clean per rules above.

## Fixtures

When adding tests, create golden YAML under `tests/fixtures/spec/` or `tests/fixtures/elements/` from HA spec examples (and ODL where it adds cases). Do not search the workspace for `supported_types.md` elsewhere.
